üü¢ BASIC MCQs (10)
1. A digital signature primarily provides:
A. Confidentiality
B. Integrity and authentication
C. Availability
D. Compression

2. Digital signatures are created using:
A. Sender‚Äôs public key
B. Receiver‚Äôs public key
C. Sender‚Äôs private key
D. Receiver‚Äôs private key

